text: The Moor may refer to: * Personification of the Moors, in their collective role as a medieval political force ==Geography== * The Moor, the core street of The Moor Quarter of Sheffield, England * The Moor, Hawkhurst, the green within The Moor Quarter's village and civil parish, England ==Arts, entertainment, and media== * Othello (character), often referred to as "The Moor", e.g., by Shakespeare * The Moor (novel) (1998) by L.R. King * "The Moor" (The Borgias) (2011), episode of the television series ==See also== *Moor (disambiguation)
